<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SIMI MAN ARRESTED IN SHASTA COUNTY DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Simi Valley man was arrested in Redding in the death of a Cottonwood man, 
Shasta County sheriff's officers said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Detective Sgt. Rusty Brewer said Eric Warner, 25, was arrested in connection 
with the death of Felix Wusstig, 38, who was found dead Dec. 12 in his 
burned-out pickup truck near a Coleman Fish Hatchery. 
</P>
<P>
Brewer said Warner, Wusstig and a third man, who was being sought, were 
searching for wood to cut when they got into a dispute in which alcohol was 
involved. Wusstig apparently was shot in the neck, and his body and truck were 
set afire, officers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
