<HEADLINE>
<P>
LERNER ON STATUS QUO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After reading Lerner's long discourse on the need for fresh approaches to the 
ills of society, there is to my mind one salient feature to his views: He 
applies the term socialism to what has long been described in the classic 
philosophies as "civic virtue." 
</P>
<P>
Why not use the established classical terminology, with the realization that 
the civic virtue involved contemplates the human race as the citizenry, and 
planet Earth as the region inhabited? That would certainly be consistent with 
the fundamental Jewish hope that all mankind will accept the rule of a 
universal God of justice. 
</P>
<P>
LARRY SELK 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
