<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to Conrad's continuing coat-hanger commentary on the Republican 
Party (Jan. 28) and the Supreme Court (previous cartoons): 
</P>
<P>
Let him also depict the other side -- the innocent, defenseless human being 
within the uterus as the hands of the doctor (who has taken an oath to preserve 
life) approach with instruments to scrape, salinize or vacuum the child out. 
</P>
<P>
Sadly, in these times of self-seeking attitudes, the unborn are treated as 
nonexistent or unimportant. 
</P>
<P>
They are the product of conception and a woman's property and lacking civil 
rights. 
</P>
<P>
Pro-choice is a misnomer; the child has no choice. One day abortion will be 
recognized for what it is -- sanitized, sanctioned murder -- and it will hang 
heavy on the conscience of the nation. 
</P>
<P>
DONNA EVICK 
</P>
<P>
Culver City 
</P>
