<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Landmark Bancorp: The La Habra-based parent company of Landmark Bank reported 
that net income for 1989 rose 41%, to $1.8 million from $1.3 million a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Net income for the fourth quarter declined 2%, to $436,000, which included a 
one-time charge to operations of $453,000 to accelerate depreciation on data 
processing equipment, and a reduction in income tax expense of $250,000, 
resulting from an accounting change. In 1988, the company recorded net income 
of $447,000 for the fourth quarter. Assets at the end of 1989 totaled $173.1 
million, 17% higher than the $148.2 million reported at the end of 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
