<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Missing Anchors Resign: Two Waco, Tex., television news anchors who were 
reported missing last week and then turned up together in New Mexico have 
resigned from the television station KWTX-TV. 
</P>
<P>
The anchors, Wendy Sheldon and Mike Reeder, gave notice Friday during their 
first meeting with station executives since they left in January, said Virgil 
Teter, the station's vice president for news. Police began looking for Reeder, 
a weekend anchor, when a company car he checked out Jan. 26 was found abandoned 
at a nearby medical center. The two anchors were found at an Albuquerque, N.M., 
hotel the following Monday. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
