BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ford May Build Trucks With Mazda: Ford Motor Co. said it is in talks with Mazda 
Motor Corp. to jointly build a new compact pickup truck. A Ford spokesman 
declined to give a specific production time for the vehicle, other than to say 
it would be in the 1990s but added that Ford favored a U.S. production site. 
The trade publication Automotive News, citing Ford planning documents, said the 
new vehicle will debut in the 1995 model year to replace the Ford Ranger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
