</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Honda Considers Selling Chryslers: Honda Motor Co. is considering a request by 
Chrysler Corp. to market the American manufacturer's automobiles in Japan, a 
Honda spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Honda spokesman Hitoshi Dewa said Chrysler suggested that the two companies set 
up a joint venture. All other details, including the Chrysler models, number of 
sales and distribution channels in Japan have yet to be completed, Dewa said. 
Nihon Keizai Shimbun, Japan's largest business journal, said Honda will 
concentrate on selling 5,000 to 6,000 Chrysler Jeeps and Cherokees a year 
through one of Honda's three distribution networks in Japan. 
</P>
