<P>
A Harbor City teen-ager has been sentenced to 27 years to life in prison for 
the fatal drive-by shooting of a 16-year-old boy who was killed as he walked 
home from his Wilmington church two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
Hector Acuna Garcia, 18, received the maximum sentence in Long Beach Superior 
Court for the murder of Rafael Pereda, who was killed moments after he left a 
youth meeting at Holy Family Catholic Church in March, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Garcia, who was 17 at the time of the murder, also has been sentenced to 37 
years to life in prison for a double murder in a drive-by shooting in August, 
1988. The two sentences will run consecutively, bringing Garcia's prison 
sentence to a total of 64 years to life. 
