<HEADLINE>
<P>
BLAST, FIRE REPORTED AT SOVIET POWER PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A unit at one of the biggest hydroelectric stations in the Transcaucasus region 
has exploded, the official news agency Tass said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The explosion collapsed the roof of the station at Mingechaur in the Soviet 
republic of Azerbaijan, 270 miles northwest of Baku, and a fire broke out, Tass 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
