<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARKLEY TALKED INTO JOINING ALL-STARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHILADELPHIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Barkley of the Philadelphia 76ers said Monday he will bow to league 
pressure and play in the NBA All-Star game on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Barkley announced Sunday he would skip the game to rest, saying a strained leg 
muscle had nagged him for several days. 
</P>
<P>
He heard from the NBA Monday. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm going to play," he said. "They gave me a play-or-else deal. They said I 
would be suspended next week if I play this week and miss the the game. I don't 
agree with them, but I've got to go." 
</P>
<P>
The injury, originally diagnosed as a groin pull, hobbled Barkley on Sunday. In 
a 114-89 victory over the Jazz on Monday, he played only 27 minutes but scored 
16 points and had eight rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
