<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sweden was eliminated in the first round of Davis Cup tennis competition when 
Italy's Paolo Cane beat Mats Wilander, 6-4, 3-6, 4-6, 7-5, 7-5, in a 4-hour 
37-minute match played over two days. 
</P>
<P>
Cane's victory gave Italy a 3-2 upset victory in the competition at Cagliari, 
Sardinia. 
</P>
<P>
The loss marks the first time since 1983 that Sweden failed to reach the Davis 
Cup finals. Italy advances to the quarterfinals and will play Austria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Before the FallPaolo Cane lies outstretched during his upset of Mats 
Wilander that gave Italy a first-round Davis Cup victory over Sweden. Sweden 
had been in the final every year since 1983. In Newswire. Reuters 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
