</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
INJUNCTIONS; NATIONAL FOOTBALL LEAGUE; FOOTBALL PLAYERS; SUITS; FREE AGENTS 
(SPORTS) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020690-0112 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 172464 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 6, 1990, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 10; Column 3; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
34 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lyudmila Narozhilenko set a world record for the women's indoor 60-meter 
hurdles with a time of 7.71 seconds at Soviet Union Indoor Athletics 
Championship at Chelyabinsk, the Tass news agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
