<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RUIZ LEADS KENNEDY OVER SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Junior point guard Valerie Ruiz scored 39 points, including six three-point 
shots, and had 11 steals to lead Kennedy High School to a 70-42 victory over 
host Santiago in a Garden Grove League girls' basketball game Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Michelle Harris added 15 points for Kennedy (12-10, 8-4). 
</P>
<P>
Becky Alcock had 21 points for Santiago (6-15, 3-9). 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League girls' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 82, Bolsa Grande 33 -- Amy Jalewalia had 36 points, 10 rebounds and 
four assists as host La Quinta (21-2, 12-0) won its 52nd consecutive league 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 62, Los Amigos 56 -- Shellie Tsuji had 19 points for visiting 
Rancho Alamitos. Garden Grove 50, Pacifica 33 -- Melanie Dear had 17 points and 
11 rebounds for host Garden Grove (11-9, 7-5). 
</P>
