<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA QUINTA GETS FIRST VICTORY OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Quinta High School won its first boys' basketball game of the season Monday 
night, defeating Bolsa Grande, 73-68, in an overtime Garden Grove League game 
at La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta's Lloyd Bennett tied the score with a jump shot with about 18 seconds 
remaining in regulation. 
</P>
<P>
Justin Sogoian had 27 points and 12 rebounds for La Quinta (1-19 overall and 
1-11 in the Garden Grove League), which was the only winless team in the 
county. 
</P>
<P>
"We've played well enough to win quite a few games and finally had a couple of 
things fall our way," La Quinta Coach Jim Perry said. 
</P>
<P>
Hinh Bui scored 22 points and Sy Sayarath scored 21 for Bolsa Grande (7-12, 
5-7). 
</P>
</TEXT>
