<TEXT>
<P>
Eastman Kodak Co. today announced a loss of $60 million in 1989's fourth 
quarter, only the third time in the photographic giant's history that it has 
reported red ink. 
</P>
<P>
The company attributed the loss, which totaled 19 cents a share, mainly to the 
costs of a restructuring program begun earlier in the year. It had earnings of 
$312 million, or 96 cents per share, in the fourth quarter of 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Sales for the fourth quarter totaled $4.89 billion, up 8% from $4.54 billion in 
the 1988 period. 
