THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
S.F. JURY SUBPOENAS LUKENBILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Subpoenas have been issued to developer Gregg Lukenbill and others to appear 
before a San Francisco grand jury investigating the financing of the campaign 
that defeated a measure to build a new baseball stadium for the Giants. 
</P>
<P>
San Francisco Dist. Atty. 
</P>
<P>
Arlo Smith said "four or five" subpoenas were issued Monday at the request of 
the grand jury. The investigation grew out of charges by Mayor Art Agnos 
shortly before election day last November that the Sacramento developer was 
trying to steal the baseball team. 
</P>
<P>
Lukenbill, apparently surprised by the news of the subpoenas, said he had no 
comment. 
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged Friday that he helped raise funds that paid for last-minute 
mail brochures that urged San Franciscans to vote against Measure P, which 
would have paved the way for a replacement for Candlestick Park. The measure 
was defeated by fewer than 2,000 votes, and the Giants have begun negotiations 
with Santa Clara. 
</P>
